{"title_page": "Compaq C series", "text_new": "{{Infobox Mobile phone\n| image           = Compaq 2000C with dock.jpg\n| name            = Compaq C series\n| slogan          = \n| manufacturer    = [[Compaq]]\n| carrier         = \n| available       = 1998 \n| screen          = 640 x 240 [[Super-twisted nematic display|STN]], 256 colours\n| camera          =\n| operatingsystem = [[Windows CE]]\n| input           = Resistive [[touchscreen]]\n| cpu             = 75&nbsp;MHz RISC [[MIPS architecture|MIPS]] processor\n| memory          = 16 MB [[Read-only memory|ROM]]<br>8 MB RAM (810c)<br>20 MB RAM (2010c)\n| memory_card     = [[PC Card]]\n| networks        = \n| connectivity    = [[IrDA]], 33.6 kbps [[Modem]]\n| battery         = 2 [[NiMH]] batteries \n| size            = 3.4 x 18.6 x 10 cm (810c)<br>4.1 x 18.6 x 10 cm (2010c)\n| weight          = 395g(810c)<br>430g(2010c)\n| series          = [[Handheld PC]]\n| predecessor     = [[Compaq Aero]]\n| successor       = [[iPAQ]]\n| related         = [[HP Jornada]]<br>[[Compaq Aero]]\n}}\n\nThe '''Compaq C series''' was a series of [[Handheld PC]]s running on [[Windows CE|Windows CE 2.0]],<ref name=CompaqPage>[http://h18004.www1.hp.com/products/quickspecs/10018_div/10018_div.HTML Official Compaq C-Series page]</ref> manufactured by [[Compaq]] from 1998.<ref>[https://www.amazon.com/dp/B00000JFEZ Compaq C-Series - Amazon]</ref>\n\n==Description==\nThe C series replaced the [[Compaq Aero|Aero line of handheld PCs]]. It was succeeded, as with other HPCs manufactured by Compaq and HP, by the [[HP iPAQ|iPAQ]] line of [[Pocket PC]]s.\n\nThe C series featured an integrated 33.6kbit/s [[modem]].<ref name=CompaqPage/> For wireless data transfer, it sported an [[IrDA]] port.\n\nAn upgrade to Windows CE 2.11 could be purchased from Compaq for US$109.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.fmcpherson.com/knowce/where/where2.htm |title=Upgrades for Windows CE devices |access-date=2011-08-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120331121412/http://www.fmcpherson.com/knowce/where/where2.htm |archive-date=2012-03-31 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n[[Targus (corporation)|Targus Inc.]] manufactured a leather portfolio case for the C series, under the Compaq brand.<ref>[http://reviews.cnet.com/cases-bags/compaq-c-series-portfolio/1707-19214_7-358280.html Compaq C-Seriesportfolio case - CNET]</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Compaq Computer Corporation]]\n[[Category:Windows CE]]\n[[Category:Windows CE devices]]\n\n\n{{compu-mobile-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Mobile phone\n| image           = Compaq 2000C with dock.jpg\n| name            = Compaq C series\n| slogan          = \n| manufacturer    = [[Compaq]]\n| carrier         = \n| available       = 1998 \n| screen          = 640 x 240 [[Super-twisted nematic display|STN]], 256 colours\n| camera          =\n| operatingsystem = [[Windows CE]]\n| input           = Resistive [[touchscreen]]\n| cpu             = 75&nbsp;MHz RISC [[MIPS architecture|MIPS]] processor\n| memory          = 16 MB [[Read-only memory|ROM]]<br>8 MB RAM (810c)<br>20 MB RAM (2010c)\n| memory_card     = [[PC Card]]\n| networks        = \n| connectivity    = [[IrDA]], 33.6 kbps [[Modem]]\n| battery         = 2 [[NiMH]] batteries \n| size            = 3.4 x 18.6 x 10 cm (810c)<br>4.1 x 18.6 x 10 cm (2010c)\n| weight          = 395g(810c)<br>430g(2010c)\n| series          = [[Handheld PC]]\n| predecessor     = [[Compaq Aero]]\n| successor       = [[iPAQ]]\n| related         = [[HP Jornada]]<br>[[Compaq Aero]]\n}}\n\nThe '''Compaq C series''' was a series of [[Handheld PC]]s running on [[Windows CE|Windows CE 2.0]],<ref name=CompaqPage>[http://h18004.www1.hp.com/products/quickspecs/10018_div/10018_div.HTML Official Compaq C-Series page]</ref> manufactured by [[Compaq]] from 1998.<ref>[https://www.amazon.com/dp/B00000JFEZ Compaq C-Series - Amazon]</ref>\n\n==Description==\nThe C series replaced the [[Compaq Aero|Aero line of handheld PCs]]. It was succeeded, as with other HPCs manufactured by Compaq and HP, by the [[HP iPAQ|iPAQ]] line of [[Pocket PC]]s.\n\nThe C series featured an integrated 33.6kbit/s [[modem]].<ref name=CompaqPage/> For wireless data transfer, it sported an [[IrDA]] port.\n\nAn upgrade to Windows CE 2.11 could be purchased from Compaq for US $109.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.fmcpherson.com/knowce/where/where2.htm |title=Upgrades for Windows CE devices |access-date=2011-08-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120331121412/http://www.fmcpherson.com/knowce/where/where2.htm |archive-date=2012-03-31 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n[[Targus (corporation)|Targus Inc.]] manufactured a leather portfolio case for the C series, under the Compaq brand.<ref>[http://reviews.cnet.com/cases-bags/compaq-c-series-portfolio/1707-19214_7-358280.html Compaq C-Seriesportfolio case - CNET]</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Compaq Computer Corporation]]\n[[Category:Windows CE]]\n[[Category:Windows CE devices]]\n\n\n{{compu-mobile-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eDescription:Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: US $ \u2192 US$", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Compaq_C_series"}
{"title_page": "2019\u201320 Hrvatski telekom Premijer liga", "text_new": "{{Infobox basketball league season\n| updated      = 1 April 2020\n| prevseason  =  [[2018\u201319 Premijer liga|2018\u201319]]\n| nextseason   = ''[[2021\u201322 Hrvatski telekom Premijer liga|2021\u201322]]'' \n| title        = Hrvatski telekom Premijer liga \n| image        = \n| caption      = \n| season       = 2020\u201321\n| champions    =\n| runners_up   =\n| semifinalists = \n| promoted      = \n| relegated     = \n| teams        = 12\n| games        = 11\n| duration     = September 2020 \u2013 May 2021<br /><small>(Regular season)</small><br />May \u2013 June 2021<br /><small>(Playoffs)</small> \n| TV           = [[Croatian Radiotelevision|HRT]]<br />[[Arena Sport]]\n| top_seed     = \n| MVP          = \n| finals_MVP   =\n| top_scorer   =   \n| rebounds_leader =  \n| assists_leader   = \n| highest_scoring  = \n| winning_streak   = \n| losing_streak   = \n| biggest_home_win   = \n| biggest_away_win   =\n| highest_attendance = \n| lowest_attendance   = \n| average_attendance   = \n}}\nThe '''2020\u201321 Hrvatski telekom Premijer liga''' will be the 29th season of the [[HT Premijer liga]], the highest professional [[basketball]] league in Croatia. The regular season is scheduled to start in September 2020 and will end in May 2021. The playoffs will begin in May 2021, and will end with the Finals in June 2021.\n\nOn 1 April 2020, the Board of Directors of the [[Croatian Basketball Federation]], in agreement with the management of the clubs under their jurisdiction, decided to cancel the 2019\u201320 competitive season. Therefore, the 2019\u201320 season will play from September 2020 to June 2021.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.hks-cbf.hr/hks/2020/odluka-o-prekidu-svih-natjecanja-pod-ingerencijom-hks-a-za-sezonu-2019-20/ |title=Odluka o prekidu svih natjecanja pod ingerencijom HKS-a za sezonu 2019./20. |website=www.hks-cbf.hr |date=1 April 2020 |accessdate=1 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Format==\nAll participants in Premijer liga including teams that play [[ABA League]] joined the regular season. It will play with a triple round-robin format where the eight first qualified teams joined the playoffs, while the penultimate will be play relegation playoffs and last qualified one was relegated.\n\n==Current teams==\n===Promotion and relegation===\n;Teams promoted from the [[2018\u201319 Croatian First Basketball League|First League]] \n*[[KK Dubrava|Dubrava Furnir]]{{Cref2|Note 1}}\n*[[KK Sonik-Puntamika|Sonik Puntamika]]\n;Teams relegated to the [[2019\u201320 Croatian First Basketball League|First League]] \n*[[KK Bosco|Bosco]] \n*[[KK Cedevita Junior|Cedevita Junior]]{{Cref2|Note 1}}\n\n===Venues and locations===\n{{location map+ |Croatia|width=400 |caption=Location of teams in the 2019\u201320 HT Premijer liga |places=\n{{Location map~ |Croatia|lat=43.7   |long=16.63   |label={{Nowrap|[[KK Alkar|Alkar]]}}|position=top}}\n{{Location map~ |Croatia|lat=44.31 |long=15.23  |label={{Nowrap|[[KK Sonik-Puntamika|Sonik Puntamika]]}}|position=bottom}}\n{{Location map~ |Croatia|lat=44.31 |long=15.23  |label={{Nowrap|[[KK Zadar|Zadar]]}}|position=top}}\n{{Location map~ |Croatia|lat=45.8   |long=15.96   |label='''Zagreb'''|position=top}}\n{{location map~ |Croatia|lat=43.73 |long=15.92 |label={{Nowrap|[[GKK \u0160ibenik|\u0160ibenka]]}} |position=left}}\n{{location map~ |Croatia|lat=43.5 |long=16.43 |label={{Nowrap|[[KK Split|Split]]}} |position=right }}\n{{location map~ |Croatia|lat=45.7 |long=16.06 |label={{Nowrap|[[KK Gorica|Gorica]]}} |position=bottom}} \n{{location map~ |Croatia|lat=45.33 |long=14.518 |label={{Nowrap|[[KK \u0160krljevo|\u0160krljevo]]}} |position=right}}\n{{location map~ |Croatia|lat=45.56 |long=18.68 |label={{Nowrap|[[KK Vrijednosnice Osijek|Vrijednosnice]]}} |position=left}}\n{{location map~ |Croatia|lat=46.03 |long=15.92 |label={{Nowrap|[[KK Zabok|Zabok]]}} |position=top }}\n{{Location map~|Yugoslavia|mark=TransparentPlaceholder.png|lat=46