etball League]]\n*[[2019\u201320 Croatian Women's Basketball League]]\n;Teams\n* [[2019\u201320 GKK \u0160ibenik season|2019\u201320 GKK \u0160ibenka season]]\n\n== Notes ==\n{{Cnote2 Begin|liststyle=disc}}\n{{Cnote2|Note 1|After the end of the previous season, [[KK Cedevita|Cedevita]] decided to move to [[Ljubljana]], Slovenia and agreed with Slovenian club [[KK Olimpija|Olimpija Ljubljana]] to make a fusion and establish the new Slovenian club [[KK Cedevita Olimpija|Cedevita Olimpija]].<ref>{{cite web |title=VIDEO: SADA JE I SLU\u017dBENO: ODR\u017dAN POVIJESNI SASTANAK U LJUBLJANI! SPAJAJU SE CEDEVITA I KK OLIMPIJA 'Ovo nikada nitko nije napravio u nijednom sportu' |url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/kosarka/video-sada-je-i-sluzbeno-odrzan-povijesni-sastanak-u-ljubljani-spajaju-se-cedevita-i-kk-olimpija-ovo-nikada-nitko-nije-napravio-u-nijednom-sportu/8964494/ |website=sportske.jutarnji.hr |accessdate=4 June 2019}}</ref> As well, [[KK Cedevita Junior|Cedevita Junior]] is formed in Zagreb. The current Cedevita Junior is not a direct fused Cedevita follow-up, which is why the [[Croatian Basketball Federation]] did not approve of Cedevita Junior's performance in the 2019\u201320 season. Instead of Cedevita Junior, [[KK Dubrava|Dubrava]] was promoted to the first tier.<ref>{{cite web |title=HKS: Cedevita Junior ne mo\u017ee igrati Premijer ligu, bio bi to neprihvatljiv presedan |url=https://sportnet.rtl.hr/vijesti/525035/kosarka-1-hkl/hks-cedevita-junior-ne-moze-igrati-premijer-ligu-bio-bi-to-neprihvatljiv-presedan/ |website=sportnet.rtl.hr |accessdate=19 June 2019 |language=hr}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Priop\u0107enje Hrvatskog ko\u0161arka\u0161kog saveza |url=https://www.hks-cbf.hr/vijesti/2019/priopcenje-hrvatskog-kosarkaskog-saveza-2 |website=hks-cbf.hr |accessdate=19 June 2019|language=hr}}</ref>}}\n{{Cnote2 End}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.hks-cbf.hr Official Site] \n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20180614011808/http://